sudo checkinstall --install --fstrans=disable --addso

sudo checkinstall --addso --install=no --fstrans=no

       --install Toggle installation of the created package.

       --fstrans Enable/disable filesystem translation. Filesystem translation enabled causes the install 					 to proceed  in a temporary directory, thus not actually touching your system.

       --provides Features provided by this package (currently only on RPM and Deb).

       --requires Dependencies required by this package.

       --addso   Search for any shared libs and add them to /etc/ld.so.conf

       --exclude Exclude these files/directories from the package.

       --include Force the inclusion in the package of the files/dirs listed in the argument (a file).

       --inspect Inspect the package's file list

       --bk      Backup any overwritten files

       --backup  Toggle backup






